The paper deals with face detection, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses neural networks to perform the detection and calibration, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the trade-off between speed and accuracy, which is a common concern in machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments involve evaluating the performance of the method on image datasets, which is a common task in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with detecting faces in unconstrained environments, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
